  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    DOMParser
    The design of DOMParser, as a class that needs to be constructed and then have its parseFromString() method called, is an unfortunate historical artifact.
    Location
    The location (URL) of the object it is linked to.
    MessageEventSource
    MessageEventSource interface.
    Navigator
    The state and the identity of the user agent.
    Screen
    A screen, usually the one on which the current window is being rendered, and is obtained using window.screen.
    Window
    A window containing a DOM document; the document property points to the DOM document loaded in that window.
